<h7><p>Arguments for</p></h7>
    <ol id="targetspotting">
    <list class="answerList">
	<li><g id="t1">Increased agricultural productivity</g></li>
    <li><g id="t2">Greater profits for the agriculture industry</g></li>
    <li><g id="t3">GM crops could be grown in difficult environments such as semi-desert</g></li>
    <li><g id="t4">Tampering with nature is nothing new in agriculture</g></li>
    <li><g id="t5">GM crops last longer in storage</g></li>
    <li><g id="t6">Farmers of GM crops are less dependent on environmentally harmful insecticides</g></li>
    <li><g id="t7">Improved flavour and appearance of GM foods</g></li>
    <li><g id="t8">Improved nutritional value of GM foods</g></li></list>
	</ol>
  
  <h7><p>Arguments against</p></h7>

    <ol id="targetspotting">    
    <list class="answerList"><li><g id="t9">GM crops interfere with nature</g></li>
    <li><g id="t10">Farming in previously uncultivated areas such as semi- desert may damage natural balance of nature</g></li>
    <li><g id="t11">Non-GM farmers will go out of business</g></li>
    <li><g id="t12">Traditional farming methods will disappear</g></li>
    <li><g id="t13">GM crops may cause ecological damage (e.g. kill harmless insects)</g></li>
    <li><g id="t14">Taste and appearance of GM foods is unnatural</g></li>
    <li><g id="t15">GM foods may be bad for our health</g></li></list>
	</ol>
</section>
